'From Squeak3.10alpha of 30 March 2007 [latest update: #7105] on 12 May 2007 at 5:29:52 pm'!"Reporter: blackSummary: 0006438: Interval>>reverseDo: is brokenDescription: interval>>reverseDo: is broken when the upper bound of the interval is not one of its element.For example, (1 to: 10 by: 2) reverseDo: executes the block for elements 10, 8, 6, 4, and 2.Tests and a fix are attached.Additional Information: Maybe reverse: should be re-defined on Intervals to answer an Interval, then foo reverseDo: could be defined as foo reverse do:Rounding errors may cause clight inconsistencies if one uses floating point numbers with intervals."!ReleaseBuilderFor3dot10 new updatePackages: 'Collections-edc.84(83).mcdCollectionsTests-edc.70(69).mcd'!